race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. INVAHIR (2) is a consistent conveyance who has hit the frame in nine of his past ten starts and rarely puts in a poor one. Gets the reliable Webster/Tilley combination and only needs some luck from the wide draw to play a major role in the outcome. SUNNYCOAST (1) is a ten-time winner who has been racing in a rich vein of form of late. Goes well at the trip and should be right there at the business end. KING JESTER (5) is a bit of a hit or miss type but is more than capable enough on his day. Should be underestimated. The well-related ENTREPRENEURIAL (7) (three-quarter to G3 winner and G2 placed Vibrant Rouge) has placed two of three over this distance range and looks one for the exotics players. UNDER THE LIMIT (6) handles all going and may make his presence felt.
